Detailed Description

This class represents the objective functional of a multilayer perceptron for the catenary problem. This is a variational problem with one input and one output variables, two boundary conditions, and an objective functional with one constraint and requiring the integration of two functions.

See also:
ObjectiveFunctional.

Constructor & Destructor Documentation

Flood::CatenaryProblem::CatenaryProblem ( MultilayerPerceptron *  newMultilayerPerceptron  ) 

General constructor. It creates a catenary problem objective functional associated to a multilayer perceptron. It also initializes all the problem parameters to their default values:

  • xA = 0.0.
  • yA = 1.0.
  • xB = 1.0.
  • yB = 1.0.
  • Length goal = 1.5.
  • Potential energy weight = 1.0.
  • Length error weight = 1.00.
  • Tolerance = 1.0e-15.
  • Initial size = 1e3.

Parameters:
newMultilayerPerceptron Pointer to a multilayer perceptron object.

Flood::CatenaryProblem::CatenaryProblem ( void   ) 

Default constructor. It creates a catenary problem objective functional not associated to any multilayer perceptron. It also initializes all the problem parameters to their default values:

  • xA = 0.0
  • yA = 1.0
  • xB = 1.0
  • yB = 1.0
  • Length goal = 1.5
  • Potential energy weight = 1.0
  • Length error weight = 1.00
  • Tolerance = 1.0e-15
  • Initial size = 1e3
